security: Disclosing the specific files and internal routing could reveal the CIA's areas of focus and operational methods concerning the JFK assassination records. Also, confirming that HQS will provide the requested information shows internal processes. Specifically, the cable includes the file number "785-120-034", which could indicate the subject matter of the file, and mentions a HUM 4-82 document which could give insight to sources. Quoting the reference to  *COMPLIANCE WITH PRESIDENT<JFK ASSASSINATION>RECORDS COLLECTION ACT." further implicates a process.
summary: A secret cable from the Vienna station of the CIA to the Director, requesting confirmation on whether Headquarters will provide further information related to compliance with the President John F. Kennedy Assassination Records Collection Act.
summary_one_paragraph: This secret cable, sent from the CIA's Vienna station on November 9, 1995, seeks confirmation from the Director regarding a previous request (VIENNA 27471) for information to assist in compliance with the President John F. Kennedy Assassination Records Collection Act. The message, routed to various internal offices including the LIMIT Chief/OCC and C/EUR/SA, inquires whether Headquarters can fulfill the request and references file 785-120-034, which is classified under reason 1.5(C) and declassified on X1, derived from HUM 4-82.
title: Request for Further Information
